        "content": "<p>The <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/blob/8fbf296d9a50aaf7ea56832ac208a4ed6bbcae8e/src/group_theory/coset.lean#L145\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/blob/8fbf296d9a50aaf7ea56832ac208a4ed6bbcae8e/src/group_theory/coset.lean#L145\">equivalence relation used</a> when <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/blob/8fbf296d9a50aaf7ea56832ac208a4ed6bbcae8e/src/group_theory/coset.lean#L160\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/blob/8fbf296d9a50aaf7ea56832ac208a4ed6bbcae8e/src/group_theory/coset.lean#L160\">defining quotient groups</a> is <code>λ x y, x⁻¹ * y ∈ &lt;subgroup&gt;</code>. But <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/blob/8fbf296d9a50aaf7ea56832ac208a4ed6bbcae8e/src/group_theory/subgroup.lean#L443\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/blob/8fbf296d9a50aaf7ea56832ac208a4ed6bbcae8e/src/group_theory/subgroup.lean#L443\">lemmas like <code>one_iff_ker_inv</code></a> in <code>subgroup.lean</code> are stated in the form <code>f a = f b ↔ f (a * b⁻¹) = 1</code> with the inverse on the right. Are lemmas such as <code>f a = f b ↔ f (a⁻¹ * b) = 1</code> in mathlib? If not, what is a suitable name for them? <code>one_iff_ker_inv'</code>?</p>",
